 Project Title: Secure Blockchain-Based Remote Voting System
ğŸ” Project Overview:
This project is a next-generation online voting system built to ensure secure, transparent, and verifiable remote voting, particularly for citizens who are unable to vote in their allocated constituency. It leverages multi-factor authentication, AI-powered facial recognition, OTP-based identity validation, and blockchain technology for tamper-proof vote recording.

ğŸ” Key Features & Functionalities:
Voter Authentication:
âœ… Verifies Aadhaar and Voter ID with MySQL database
âœ… Uses Firebase Authentication to send OTP to registered phone number
âœ… Voter OTP stored with expiry (1 min) and validated
âœ… Face detection and verification implemented with confidence threshold

Secure One-Time URL (OTU):
âœ… OTU is generated and hashed using SHA-256
âœ… Stored in MySQL with expiry (10 minutes)
âœ… Used for navigation to face-capture & voting page
âœ… Hashed OTU's private key used for final vote confirmation

Facial Recognition:
âœ… Real-time camera input with optimized video settings
âœ… Uses face-api.js with SSD MobileNet model
âœ… Implements 0.7 confidence threshold for reliable detection
âœ… Stores face descriptors in session storage for verification
âœ… Processes voter photos for database storage with error handling

AI-Powered Voter Monitoring:
âœ… Detects multiple faces in frame
âœ… Validates face detection confidence scores
âœ… Real-time feedback during face capture
âœ… Enhanced error handling and user feedback

Blockchain Vote Recording:
- Votes are securely stored in Polygon (Ethereum Layer 2) blockchain
- IPFS is optionally used for decentralized vote storage
- Ensures tamper-proof auditability and transparency

Vote Confirmation:
âœ… Face verification before vote submission
âœ… Session-based face descriptor validation
- Blockchain transaction confirmation pending
- Vote receipt generation pending

Admin Monitoring Dashboard:
- Real-time tracking of votes
- Alerts based on AI and logs via blockchain and local DB

